From: Volodymyr Babchuk <volodymyr_babchuk@epam.com>
Date: Thu, 17 Oct 2024 22:20:34 +0300
Subject: [PATCH v3 24/24] [TEMP] arch-arm: change MFIS interrupt number to 256

This IRQ number is reserved on gen4

TODO: Make it configurable (via toolstack, maybe?)

Signed-off-by: Volodymyr Babchuk <volodymyr_babchuk@epam.com>
---
 xen/include/public/arch-arm.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/xen/include/public/arch-arm.h b/xen/include/public/arch-arm.h
index 5ee99e2a3e..89c69c3c26 100644
--- a/xen/include/public/arch-arm.h
+++ b/xen/include/public/arch-arm.h
@@ -491,7 +491,7 @@ typedef uint64_t xen_callback_t;
 #define GUEST_EVTCHN_PPI        31
 
 #define GUEST_VPL011_SPI        32
-#define GUEST_MFIS_SPI          265 /* "Reserved" on Gen3 */
+#define GUEST_MFIS_SPI          256 /* "Reserved" on Gen4 */
 
 #define GUEST_VIRTIO_MMIO_SPI_FIRST   33
 #define GUEST_VIRTIO_MMIO_SPI_LAST    43
